Sorts the DPO list by the specified attribute values. The first attribute in the attribute_list has the highest sort precedence. Each attribute can be a chain identical to what get_db supports. A leading "." is optional, so all the following commands presenting the use of attribute_list specify legal arguments for an inst list: 
 sort_db insts name 
 sort_db insts .name 
 sort_db insts {location.x location.y} 
 sort_db insts {.location.x .location.y}

