Specifies the name of the view. This view will be saved in libname/cellname/ that you specified with restoreDesign or init_design . This option provides a shortcut to save a view quickly in the same libName/cellName structure that you restored. 
 Example : restoreDesign -write_db -oa_view {designLib top layout}

write_db -oa_view {designLib top place}
write_db -oa_view place 
 Both the above write_db commands are equivalent.

Adds the specified hosts to the rsh/ssh configuration. If you specify more than one host, separate each host name with a space. 
 Each time you specify a host, the software uses it to run one client process. To run more than one client process on a host, specify it more than once. For example, if you have two machines that each has two CPUs and you want to use both CPUs in both machines, type a command like the following: 
 set_distributed_hosts -rsh -add { machine1 machine2 \ machine1 machine2 }

